'''
To calculate salary of an employee given his basic pay
(take as input from user).
Calculate gross salary of employee.
Let HRA be 10 % of basic pay and
TA be 5% of basic pay.
Let employee pay professional tax as 2% of total salary.
Calculate net salary payable after deductions.
'''

#take input from user
basic_pay=int(input("Enter basic pay =>"))
HRA = basic_pay * (10/100)
TA = basic_pay * (5/100)
TAX = basic_pay * (2/100)
print("HRA => ",HRA)
print("TA =>",TA)
print("TAX =>",TAX)
#calculate gross salary
gross_sal = basic_pay + HRA + TA
print("Gross salary =>",gross_sal)
#calculate net salary
net_sal = gross_sal - TAX
print("Net salary",net_sal)
